{{Infobox river | name = Takano River | name_native = | image = Takano river from hanazono bridge.JPG | image_size = 250px | image_caption = Takano river from Hanazono bridge in [[Kyoto]] | source1_location = | mouth_location = [[Kamo River]] | basin_countries = [[Japan]] | length = | source1_elevation = | mouth_elevation = | discharge1_avg = | basin_size = | river_system = [[Yodo River]] }}
The '''Takano River''' is located in [[Kyoto Prefecture]], [[Japan]].
The [[Kamo River]] and Takano River join on the Tadasu River Banks (Jp., Tadasu-gawara 糺河原). There is the "River Confluence" shrine of [[Shimogamo Shrine]], leading to the forested area called [[Tadasu no Mori|Tadasu-no-mori]]. <ref>http://www.jnto.go.jp/eng/location/regional/kyoto/takanoshuhen.html</ref> <ref>http://japanvisitor.blogspot.sk/2011/08/kamo-and-takano-rivers-kyoto.html</ref>
