The [[Kamo River]] and Takano River join on the Tadasu River Banks (Jp., Tadasu-gawara 糺河原). There is the "River Confluence" shrine of [[Shimogamo Shrine]], leading to the forested area called [[Tadasu no Mori|Tadasu-no-mori]]. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.jnto.go.jp/eng/location/regional/kyoto/takanoshuhen.html | title=Things to do in Japan &#124; Travel Japan（Japan National Tourism Organization） }}</ref> <ref>{{cite web | url=http://japanvisitor.blogspot.sk/2011/08/kamo-and-takano-rivers-kyoto.html | title=Japan Experience, a unique experience &#124; Japan Experience }}</ref>
